[3] Peru (Lambayeque region)
Date: Thu 15 Jan 2009
Source: Actualidad [Spanish, trans. Mod.TY, edited]
<http://www.peru.com/noticias/sgc/portada/2009/01/15/detalle19541.aspx>


The Lambayeque Regional Health Directorate (DIRESA) in coordination
with the Illimo municipal district, is evaluating the initiation of
fumigation of dwellings in this locality in which 2 confirmed
non-fatal dengue cases occurred.

Victor Echeandia Arellano, the official in charge of this DIRESA,
stated that the _Aedes_ index (number of vector mosquitoes per house)
is high, necessitating that they proceed with fumigation, such as was
done a year ago in Olmos district.

They have begun a community educational effort in order to prevent
spread of this disease that is worrying local authorities, he added.

It is worth noting that in the Illimo locality, they are carrying out
an aggressive campaign using abate, which is an [_Aedes_] larvacide
which eliminates the eggs [sic] of _Aedes aegypti_, which causes
[transmits] dengue [virus].

--
