[6] Paraguay (Concepcion)
Date: Fri 16 Jan 2009
Source: Tiempos de la internet [edited]
<http://www.timesoftheinternet.com/espanol/14058.html>


Paraguay health officials have assigned a team to investigate a
dengue outbreak in the Yvy Ya'u area of Concepcion department. In
this area, there are various people who have a clinical picture that
is compatible with dengue. As well, various _Aedes aegypti_
reservoirs [vectors] that transmit dengue [virus] have been found.

To date, 6 [laboratory] confirmed cases of the disease have been
found, with 104 suspected [cases] and 78 [possible cases] discarded.
In the fight against dengue, the populace has an obligation to combat
the mosquito vector by eliminating breeding sites.

According to the [news] bulletin issued following the meeting in the
situation room, the team assigned to investigate the dengue outbreak
in Yvy Ya'u presented the following situation: In that locality,
various people were found who were convalescent with clinical signs
compatible with dengue [virus infection] who had consulted with
[health workers] in the private sector, and people with acutely
febrile illnesses with a diagnosis compatible [with dengue] who were
self-medicated. The earliest case was found during the visit of 23 Dec [2008].

--
