[7] Indonesia (South Sulawesi)
Date: Sat 10 Jan 2009
Source: Liputan.com [Indonesian, machine trans., edited]
<http://www.liputan6.com/news/?id=171194&c_id=3>


The dengue fever outbreak in the Bone Regency, South Sulawesi, on
Friday [9 Jan 2009] was designated by the Kesehatan local [health]
service as an extraordinary incident [emergency]. The data of the
Health Service showed hundreds of residents, including children, had
become casualties of the [dengue virus transmitted by] _Aedes
aegypti_ mosquito bite. Moreover, 3 children under 5 years old died.

In the meantime, the number of dengue fever patients in the
Tenriawaru Hospital continued to increase, not only in the rooms of
the wards, but the hospital corridor was then filled by dengue fever patients.

At least 17 subdistricts in the Bone Regency are affected by dengue
fever illness. The most serious subdistricts were Lappariaja,
Cenrana, Dua Boccoe, Tellu Siattinge, and Barebbo.

--
