[8] Taiwan
Date: Tue 20 Jan 2009
Source: Taiwan Center for Disease Control [Chinese, edited]
<http://www.cdc.gov.tw/lp.asp?ctNode=1906&CtUnit=1084&BaseDSD=7&mp=1>


During the period 1 Jan 2008 through 6 Jan 2009 there were a total of
1419 cases reported of which 488 tested positive for [dengue
infection. In the period since the "summer" (week 24), there were
1140 cases reported of which 464 tested positive [for dengue infection].

--
Communicated by:
ProMED-mail <promed@promedmail.org>

[The China Post in its 18 Jan 2009 edition
<http://www.chinapost.com.tw/taiwan/local/taoyuan/2009/01/18/192611/Taoyuan-County.htm>
reported that there were 2 imported dengue cases, one from Thailand
and one from Indonesia, both countries endemic for dengue viruses.
Given considerable locally transmitted dengue virus in 2008, it is
likely that there is a risk of imported dengue virus initiating
ongoing, local transmission in 2009.

